                      <span >Members plan and produce four issues of </span><i><span>Get
                  the Message</span></i><span>
                  each year, soliciting articles from IPRA members and from
                  outside sources. The newsletter is mailed to all voting IPRA
                  members and to a number of out-of-state subscribers. Recent
                  surveys show that <i>Get
                  the Message</i> has one of the highest readerships of any
                  state publication. Committee
                  members are also responsible for generating flyers and
                  publicity for workshop sessions and other special events.
 </span>
                </td>
